This paper discusses the design of a dynamic network for datacenters that delivers low-latency and high-bandwidth packet delivery. The paper focuses on the network architecture and its ability to support modern applications. Given the focus on network design and datacenter applications, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the rapid and deterministic reconfiguration of the network, which suggests a focus on control systems and system dynamics, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of expander graphs, which are commonly used in information theory and coding, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the network under different workloads, which suggests a focus on performance evaluation and benchmarking, making cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) a possible sub-category as well.
